ce:section.ce:para:
Acoustic emissions in the focal region were investigated as a potential indicator of treatment success. Lysis rates were plotted against acoustic emissions in the range 2–5 MHz (Fig. 8
                        ). There was found to be a positive correlation between acoustic emissions and lysis rates. Linear fitting yielded a coefficient of R
                        2 = 0.870 with p < 0.01. It was deemed that there were insufficient data to fit more complex curves.
